Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Browse Furniture Catalog, Check Furniture Availability
   Explanation: The use case "Check Furniture Availability" is an inclusion use case that is included only by "Browse Furniture Catalog". It is not associated with any actor directly, it does not include or extend any other use case, it is not extended by any use case, and it is not involved in any generalization. "Check Furniture Availability" does not represent a complete service offering an observable result to a user on its own — it is merely a decomposed substep of browsing the catalog. This constitutes the Functional Decomposition antipattern via the include relationship, where a base use case's behavior has been unnecessarily split into an inclusion fragment that serves no independent purpose.
